														</div>
						</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-77e2b8b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="77e2b8b" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
								<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
				<h3>It&#8217;s Time to Free the Guest from the Tyranny of Choice</h3><p>Humans have a remarkable ability to over-complicate. Some studies show that the average person makes an overwhelming 35,000 choices per day.</p><p>While we all think we want more options, this comes with a paradox of choice. There is such a thing as too many options. This has certainly been true in recent years for restaurant chains that lacked the discipline to prune and <a href="https://aaronallen.com/blog/menu-strategy">manicure their menus</a>.</p>					</div>
						</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-5486bcc elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-id="5486bcc" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="image.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
								<div class="elementor-image">
													<a href="https://aaronallen.com/blog/menu-strategy">
